Lineage and acknowledgment

OpenH2O independently reimplements the methodology of the open-source
Groundwater Accounting Platform on a different stack (Django, GeoDjango,
PostgreSQL/PostGIS, Docker) and in a different programming language. That
platform is stewarded by the California Water Data Consortium and developed by
ESA (formerly Sitka Technology Group), and is likewise released under the GNU
Affero General Public License v3.

Among that platform's releases, OpenH2O's design most closely parallels the
current "Qanat" community platform (esassoc/qanat-community); it also draws on
the earlier "Rio" implementation (Rosedale-Rio Bravo, California) and the
"Zybach" sibling deployment (Natural Resources Districts, Nebraska). We are
grateful for that prior art. OpenH2O re-expresses its concepts in original
code: none of the ESA/Sitka/Qanat/Rio/Zybach source code is copied into this
repository.

